      "content": "That's a good start for the framing. To make the argument more robust, could you expand on the idea of \"technological transfer\"? Specifically, can you explain how many of those supposed \"non-Western\" advancements were actually just raw materials or primitive concepts that only truly became \"civilized\" or functional once they were refined and applied by Western scientific methodology?",
